<text id="02-output-contract" title="BA Week-One Pack Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>Pins the shape of the week-one-pack manifest. Validator parses this manifest to confirm the deliverable folder is "done".</summary>
  <section title="JSON Schema (draft-07) — pack manifest">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/ba-week-one-pack-manifest.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["project_name", "ba_name", "week_range", "files", "signoff"],
  "properties": {
    "project_name": {"type": "string", "minLength": 2},
    "ba_name": {"type": "string", "minLength": 2},
    "week_range": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$"},
    "files": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": ["inventory_md", "stakeholders_md", "glossary_md", "processes_md", "risks_md"],
      "properties": {
        "inventory_md": {"type": "object", "required": ["path", "row_count"], "properties": {"path": {"type": "string"}, "row_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1}}},
        "stakeholders_md": {"type": "object", "required": ["path", "named_rows", "approve_authority_count"], "properties": {"named_rows": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1}, "approve_authority_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1}}},
        "glossary_md": {"type": "object", "required": ["path", "term_count"], "properties": {"term_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 15}}},
        "processes_md": {"type": "object", "required": ["path", "diagram_files"], "properties": {"diagram_files": {"type": "array", "minItems": 1, "items": {"type": "string", "pattern": "\\.(png|svg)$"}}}},
        "risks_md": {"type": "object", "required": ["path", "gap_count", "risk_count"], "properties": {"gap_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 5}, "risk_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 5}}}
      }
    },
    "signoff": {
      "type": "object", "required": ["engagement_manager_name", "signoff_ts"],
      "properties": {"engagement_manager_name": {"type": "string", "minLength": 2}, "signoff_ts": {"type": "string", "format": "date-time"}}
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}
]]></code>
  </section>
  <section title="Examples">
    <example type="good" title="Valid manifest">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "project_name": "Acme Migration",
  "ba_name": "Maria Lopes",
  "week_range": "2026-05-18/2026-05-22",
  "files": {
    "inventory_md": {"path": "pack/inventory.md", "row_count": 47},
    "stakeholders_md": {"path": "pack/stakeholders.md", "named_rows": 8, "approve_authority_count": 2},
    "glossary_md": {"path": "pack/glossary.md", "term_count": 22},
    "processes_md": {"path": "pack/processes.md", "diagram_files": ["pack/processes.svg"]},
    "risks_md": {"path": "pack/risks.md", "gap_count": 5, "risk_count": 6}
  },
  "signoff": {"engagement_manager_name": "Pedro Silva", "signoff_ts": "2026-05-22T17:00:00Z"}
}
]]></code>
      <note>Required counts met; PM signoff timestamp present.</note>
    </example>
    <example type="bad" title="Invalid — missing diagram + low glossary">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{"project_name": "x", "ba_name": "x", "week_range": "x",
 "files": {"glossary_md": {"path": "g", "term_count": 4}, "processes_md": {"path": "p", "diagram_files": []}},
 "signoff": {}}
]]></code>
      <note>Glossary terms &lt; 15; processes lack diagram; signoff empty.</note>
    </example>
  </section>
  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>required file path present but row_count/term_count 0 (rule r1)</item>
      <item>stakeholders_md.approve_authority_count == 0 (rule r2)</item>
      <item>glossary_md.term_count &lt; 15 (rule r3)</item>
      <item>processes_md.diagram_files empty (rule r4)</item>
      <item>signoff.engagement_manager_name empty (rule r5)</item>
    </list>
  </section>
  <section title="Allowed transformations">
    <list>
      <item>Stakeholder authority may use RAPID (R/A/P/I/D) instead of Approve/Consult/Inform/None when consistent.</item>
      <item>Glossary may include cross-references to org glossaries with source URL + last-checked date.</item>
    </list>
  </section>
  <reference path="templates/week-one-pack-skeleton.md"/>
  <reference path="scripts/validate-ba-onboarding-week-one-template.py"/>
</text>
